We went here for a work lunch.
There was only a few other people in the restaurant so it was pretty quiet.
There were three of us and our list of lunches included the Southwest Caesar with Chicken, the Tuna Melt, and the Sliders.
When our food arrived at the table, every dish looked delicious!
We were all ooing and ahing over each other's plate.
All of the dishes were good and the service was fine.
No complaints.
I will go back when I want a tasty, quiet lunch without the hussle and bussle of other super-busy downtown lunch spots.

======   This review is for Marston's Daily Lunch Buffet - Friday!
======  It was hot downtown today, & a big glass of "Mango Iced Tea" got things off to a good start for me when I dropped into this lovely restaurant a little after noon for their lunch buffet!
After that, I went for a prepared cup of delicious fruit, which included a big blackberry!
Then it was on to the stylish salad bar, which had a number of unusual treats such as freeze-dried corn kernels (good!
), dried raspberries, delicious real bacon bits, & nice cold tomato quarters.
The salad dressing I chose, of the three, was really good too.
Next I had a Southwest Chipolte Chicken Wrap.
It was on a foofy little square plate, so I had my doubts, but it turned out to be really good, & rocketed this place up to 4-Stars for me...  & I hadn't even seen the hot table yet!
The hot food theme today was Indigenous American, & everything was different & delicious!
I started with Albondigas  Soup which was thick with tasty meatballs, rice, & flavor.
The hot vegetables were Calibacitas Stew with Cheese, & tasty pinto beans, fixed a certain good way.
Then there was Fry Bread, a chicken dish that I failed to write down the name of, but made a tasty taco with a warm flour tortilla & a bunch of other goodies that were around to add in.
Then, after some of their delicious Chimichuri Shrimp, I had room for just one of their SEVEN delicious desserts!
Lunch Buffet $12 daily, including beverage.

